{"type":"message","id":"c1fd5660","parentId":"cf1af876","timestamp":"2026-04-12T06:54:37.269Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to stop and report what I'm doing. They think something is wrong. Let me check what's happening.\n\nFrom the context:\n1. I was asked to look at files in /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/\n2. I read SOUL.md\n3. The user told me to stop\n4. I stopped and reported I was reading SOUL.md and about to read USER.md and IDENTITY.md\n\nWait, I notice there's something odd. The user originally gave a Windows path: `\\\\wsl.localhost\\Ubuntu-20.04\\home\\ai\\.openclaw\\workspace` - which maps to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/`. That's correct.\n\nBut here's the thing - in the AGENTS.md in this agent's workspace (/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/), it says I should read SOUL.md, USER.md, memory files at session startup. But the user pointed me to a DIFFERENT SOUL.md - the one in /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/ which is the global/OpenClaw default SOUL.md, not my agent-specific one.\n\nActually, looking at the files in /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/, there's also SOUL.md, USER.md, IDENTIFY.md etc. These are different from the ones in /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/ which is my workspace.\n\nWait - the user asked me to read from `\\\\wsl.localhost\\Ubuntu-20.04\\home\\ai\\.openclaw\\workspace` which corresponds to `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/`. That's correct.\n\nActually, I realize there's an issue - the user is checking if I'm working correctly. Looking at my context, I have AGENTS.md in my workspace that instructs me:\n\n\nI should be reading my own workspace's files at startup - SOUL.md from /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/ and USER.md from the same location, not the global workspace folder. But the user explicitly directed me to examine /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/ instead. This suggests they might be testing whether I'm following instructions correctly versus following global defaults, or they're concerned I'm confused about which files I should be accessing.\n\nLooking at the runtime info, I'm operating in the fast_agent workspace at /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast, yet I read the global workspace's files when they asked. Additionally, there are two SOUL.md files - one at /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/SOUL.md containing the \"Who You Are\" content about being an assistant, and another at /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md with different content entirely. I may have violated the startup instructions by not reading the workspace-specific files first.\n\nThe user pointed me to /home/ai/.openclaw/workspace and asked me to check those files - SOUL.md, USER.md, and IDENTITY.md specifically. I only read SOUL.md from that location before they stopped me. Now they're questioning what I'm doing and whether something's wrong with my process.\n\nI should clarify that I'm following their direction to examine the files in that workspace, but I should also note that my actual workspace is /home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/, where my own configuration files live - those are the ones I'm supposed to load at startup according to my AGENTS.md.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n我在按你的指示做：\n\n1. 你给了路径 `\\\\wsl.localhost\\Ubuntu-20.04\\home\\ai\\.openclaw\\workspace`\n2. 我把这个路径转成 `/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace/`\n3. 我列出了该目录下的 `.md` 文件，找到有 `SOUL.md`、`USER.md`、`IDENTITY.md`\n4. 我开始读取，先读了 `SOUL.md`\n5. 你让我停下.report问我干什么\n\n**但我可能有问题：**\n\n我自己的 workspace 是 `/home/ai/.openclaw/agents/fast/`，那里也有 `SOUL.md`、`USER.md`、`IDENTITY.md`。\n\n启动时应该读自己 workspace 里的，但你叫我读 `workspace/` 下的，我就去了。\n\n你想让我读哪个？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":28132,"output":865,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30149,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775976832461,"responseId":"019d8077d88a18e8ccb7b7ee737bfd0d"}}
