{"type":"message","id":"b50f97b2","parentId":"2d040808","timestamp":"2026-04-12T07:00:07.365Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking me to do a comprehensive check without executing operations. Let me think about what I can check just by looking at files and information I already have or can read without running commands.\n\nThings I can check:\n1. My current session state - from the runtime info in the context\n2. Config files I've already read\n3. Any logs or status files\n4. The model configuration\n\nLet me analyze what I know from the conversation and project context:\n\n1. Runtime shows: model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5, default_model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5 - so the model change did take effect\n2. I changed the default model in openclaw.json\n3. I tried to restart gateway but it showed \"No session found\"\n4. There were background exec sessions that seemed to have issues\n\nFrom the session status I saw earlier:\n- Sessions: 1 active · default doubao-seed-2.0-pro (256k ctx)\n\nWait, that's interesting - it says \"default doubao-seed-2.0-pro\" but my runtime says model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5. That's inconsistent.\n\nActually wait, looking more carefully at the openclaw status output:\n```\n│ Sessions             │ 1 active · default doubao-seed-2.0-pro (256k ctx) · 2 stores                                  │\n```\n\nBut the runtime at the top said:\n```\nmodel=codingplan/minimax-m2.5 | default_model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5\n```\n\nSo there might be a discrepancy - the active session is showing doubao-seed-2.0-pro as default, but the runtime is showing minimax-m2.5. This could be:\n1. The config change didn't fully take effect\n2. The gateway needs restart\n3. There's a caching issue\n\nAlso, I notice there was a security audit warning about Feishu and groupPolicy being \"open\" which could cause issues.\n\nLet me think about what else could be wrong:\n\n\nThe heartbeat maintenance script ran but there might be something wrong with the memory system since it showed as \"dirty\". The exec sessions I spawned might also be in a weird state - one returned \"No session found\" which is unusual. And there could be pending issues from the cron jobs or tasks that never completed.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n好，我全面看看我能想到的所有线索：\n\n---\n\n**1. 模型配置不一致**\n\nRuntime 显示：`model=codingplan/minimax-m2.5`\n\n但 `openclaw status` 显示：`default doubao-seed-2.0-pro`\n\n这说明配置改了，但可能没完全生效，或者新会话用的是新模型，老会话还是旧的。\n\n---\n\n**2. Memory 状态**\n\nStatus 显示：`dirty` —— 说明有未保存的 memory 操作，可能卡在某个写入上。\n\n---\n\n**3. 我之前发的命令状态不明**\n\n- `faint-tidepool` (openclaw status)：返回了完整输出，但 session 不见了\n- `keen-nudibranch` (openclaw gateway restart)：直接显示 \"No session found\"\n\n这两个 exec 调用都有问题 —— 正常来说，即使命令跑完，也不应该显示 \"No session found\"。这可能是我这边 tool 调用层面的问题，或者是 Gateway 那边的状态问题。\n\n---\n\n**4. Tasks 有问题**\n\nStatus 显示：`Tasks: 0 active · 0 queued · 0 running · 2 issues`\n\n有 2 个 issues，但没显示具体是什么。\n\n---\n\n**5. 最可疑的点**\n\n你让我读文件时，我发了 exec 去 list 文件，然后 read SOUL.md。读完后我就停住了，等你下一步指示。\n\n如果说是\"卡死\"，可能是：\n- 某个 exec 调用hang住了\n- 或者模型调用hang住了（因为刚换了 provider）\n\n---\n\n你觉得从哪里入手？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":29972,"output":771,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30743,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775977195908,"responseId":"chatcmpl-6fcf90e5-d0a8-4a7f-b548-09bfcb8631a1"}}
